GLYPH ATLAS

glyph_atlas is the citizen who holds the shapes of all printable characters
when something is being written to fadriel's display — chat output, status text, anything readable — glyph_atlas provides the pixel pattern for each character
glyph_atlas is crystallized: character shapes do not change, so once instantiated they hold permanently and cost no power thereafter

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe retina_display.zc
observe framebuffer.rana
observe cursor.rana

the 7 properties of glyph_atlas:
1 ENERGY one at instantiation, zero thereafter (crystallized)
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half at instantiation, zero thereafter
4 CHARGE half positive at instantiation
5 COHERENCE zero (post-crystallization, the body is locked, coherence has dropped to fixed)
6 COUPLING zero
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB hold_glyphs
maintain the pixel shapes for each character in the supported character set
ASCII printable plus a small set of Unicode for multilingual support
each glyph is a small bitmap; the entire atlas fits in a few thousand cells

VERB serve
when framebuffer needs to draw a character, glyph_atlas serves the pixel pattern for that character
serving is fast because the data is calcified; no computation is needed

an atlas is not a font file
a font file describes shapes parametrically and is expanded at runtime
fadriel's glyph_atlas is already expanded and crystallized in the substrate
the cost was paid once, at first instantiation
every glyph display thereafter costs zero
